                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia (<persName type="from"
                            >Feely</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-22T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 22, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Department’s telegram No. 30, August 20, 3 p.m. The situation here is tense
                    and because of the violent attacks of the press and a growing popular sentiment
                    against what is termed the intromission and pressure of the Neutral Commission
                    on Bolivia in favor of Paraguay, the Minister of Foreign Affairs has been
                    reluctant to discuss any suggestions with me since August 15th. I shall see him
                    today and report the result of this evening.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office has sent a circular telegram to Bolivian Legations citing six
                    cases of Paraguayan aggression since July 25th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Feely</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
